Widespread throughout Australia. |
| Neohydatothrips samayunkur     | Marigold thrips                  | Marigolds ( Calendula and Tagetes ), breeding in flowers and on leaves sometimes causing severe leaf deformation. Reported in NSW and Qld. |
| Odontothripiella australis*    | Gorse thrips                     | Various legume species including Pultenaea , Bossiaea , Jacksonia , Genista and Lupinus . Known from most of Australia, except NT. |
| Parthenothrips dracaenae       | Palm thrips                      | Various species, particularly Kentia palm, but also recorded on Ficus spp., Emilia sonchifolia (Asteraceae), the fern Adiantum formosum and species from a number of other distantly related plant families. It has been reported in NSW, Qld, SA, Tas and Vic. |
| Pezothrips kellyanus           | Kelly's citrus thrips            | Mainly citrus in SA, but also reported in NSW, Qld and WA. It has also been reported from tomatoes, various Asteraceae, Brassicaceae, Rosaceae, Pittosporum and other plants. |
| Pseudodendrothrips mori        | Parlour palm thrips              | Morus spp., including mulberry, and Ficus spp. Only recorded in Qld.